You can't log on to the database server because SQL Server isn't running. 
You've already restarted twice.
You're getting farther and farther behind.
Oh no!

DON'T PANIC!

In the Windows search box, type CMD
Command Prompt will show as an option.
RIGHT-click on it, and select "Run as administrator".
Click Yes.

When the command prompt opens, type NET START MSSQLSERVER
Wait for it to finish starting. It will tell you when it has.
Go back to SQL Server Management Studio.
Click Connect.
It should connect normally.
